The comparison of war.
The area of the settlement of the Ogoni is waged a battlefield for years: stormed here for over 60 years the first European explorers, here was the first resistance in the 1980s with the writer Ken Saro-Wiwa, later executed here had to put up its first factory the consortium Shell in 1993, because it would be too dangerous for the employees of the oil.
Yet it is nowadays forbidden the return of the businesses in Ogoniland: while daily pumped more than two million barrels of black gold across the delta region, a size three times greater than Switzerland, with more than 5,000 sources of extraction and 7,000 kilometres of pipes, the oil fields in Ogoniland were quiet, the location is too unstable to the consortium.
