"I think the bigger share of mergers has been done, the incorporation of cajasol to a group of civic banking cannot be said to be a second round, there are adjustments."
"the biggest part is completely made; maybe instead of 17 go to 13 or 14 but all the major processes have been done and tutelados by the Bank of Spain, that this has worked very well," said the manager.
In statements at a breakfast meeting of the Association of directors and executives of Aragón (adea) olavarrieta, has shown that the concentration process is addressing "the greatest speed possible, and we must be very happy as is happening at the time that in its day, not now, have been set in the plans of business with the Bank of Spain" emphasized.
"going from 45 boxes with an average of 28.500 million volume of assets to 17 with 75.500 million is a process that has no equal in history, reducing the number of entities with a 62% to be much more big to meet with Basel," stressed.
Olavarrieta acknowledged that "there are a number of views rather unfortunate on the slowness of the process" that demonstrate a "lack of seriousness and respect," because "what makes the Bank of Spain is to remember that we have to be within the deadline before the end of the year."
The Director General of the ECSC, José Antonio olavarrieta, assures yesterday that Spain has the financial system more rigorous across Europe and "probably" in the world, and attached to those who challenge a "lack of knowledge."
The manager pointed out that, within the current economic climate, "we can be very calm" with the situation of the financial institutions and the savings banks, a system that has launched a process of concentration "very important" and that "is the greatest speed possible."
Also recalled that Spanish banks it was very successful staging of the stress tests that the ECB took in July.
Zapatero and the German red line
Berlin has opted to stay in the euro, but has set the conditions for the entire Union.
Tensions in the markets have led to a double government response.
On the one hand, José Luis Rodríguez Zapatero has advanced further adjustment measures, from tax cuts to SMEs, regulation of private agencies placement or abolition of the 426 euros of aid to unemployed with no benefit to the privatisation of the 49% of aena, the management of airports of horses and the Prat and 30% of the state lotteries.
On the other, the Vice-President Elena Salgado, with the support of former Felipe González, has joined the criticism of the cancillera Angela Merkel for their role in triggering the current crisis.
How shall we interpret these moves?
Go ahead that Merkel is not a mistake in its communication policy.
On the contrary, is another twist in the difficult process of redefining the euro.
And that Germany has a new vision of what should be their future, which is at odds with that of maintaining the traditions of good part of their partners.
Compared to the European resistance, in Germany begins to especularse on three possible solutions to the crisis.
The first, a strong euro, comprised of herself, Austria and the Netherlands, among other countries, while the South would leave the currency area.
The second, the recovery of the framework, although now seems to science fiction, with a current of opinion favorable, very close to 50% of the population.
The third, a redesign of the euro, in line with the German proposals more macroeconomic control, budgetary rigour, fines to the countries violators, possible defaults of any of them and extension to the private sector of the costs of the prospective adjustments.
The German position is clear and defining comes from long ago, so now there are no excuses.
First, in 2009, when both the IMF and the European Commission estimulaban deficits, the German Government came up with a constitutional reform to prevent them from 2016.
This was the first sign of divergence between what Germany believed it should be (plans for fiscal rigour and stability in public financing), and what they were practicing their European partners, including France.
The second in the front is that given the Central European country when Merkel won took the decision to rescue of Greece.
By then, was the subject of fierce criticism, but the truth is that political consensus in Germany and the public and the published were perfectly against the rescue of Greece.
Finally, in the last few days of October, Merkel has been a clear stance, calling for the reform of the Treaties of the Union to the rescue of a country and, at the same time, forcing private lenders to pay part of the cost.
This position was interpreted as anti-European, which precipitated the Irish crisis and everything else.
But his proposal, although somewhat watered down, has been adopted and, in the coming months, we should assist the process of reform of the Union makes those measures from 2013.
Germany has drawn a red line that not cross.
And telling us all that, though it now has to take measures that perhaps is not far from agreement, from the time the former operation of the euro, it will be finished.
The 2013 will mean the birth of a new monetary area, in which the countries offenders will be severely punished, may be forced to go on suspension of payment and, in this case, the private sector, it will also run with part of the cost.
Germany is pointing out that we must keep a harsh way of growth with high rates of saving and investment, moderation in alcohol consumption, improvements in productivity and competitiveness and external balances.
Another alternative based on debt and the building, with huge holes in the balance of payments, as the who chaired the Spanish growth in the years of boom, will simply not tolerate.
The signal is clear.
And it would be wrong not to understand.
These are not just dealing with the public deficit to 3% in 2013.
What we require is much harder.
And the worst thing in these circumstances we could do is let to ourselves.
I hope that the current turbulence should switch to a calmer.
And to use the window of opportunity that we have given, until spring 2013.
It seems that the President Zapatero also has understood this and his double manifesto (the reforms promised after the meeting on Saturday with big business and the announcement yesterday of new measures) suggests that, despite the criticism of Merkel, has opened up the view that we have to order at home.
But the red line that Germany has drawn here and it seems that will move.
And, among the possibilities are there, to leave a monetary zone too atiborrada of countries that are not serious, it cannot be excluded.
Then, Germany can we always say that he had alerted.
Sport and fraud law.
Wiles as Alonso and Ramos to Ajax show ingenuity but unwilling to escape a fine.
The expulsion allegedly carefully nurtured by two players of real Madrid (xabi Alonso and Sergio Ramos) in the party contested on 23 November against Ajax in the Champions League has caused rivers of ink to write about if such behaviour is unsporting and if, eventually, both players should be sanctioned by UEFA.
As is well known, in the absence of a few minutes in the game (that his team had clearly won), the two players deliberately lost time out means to make mistakes that the referee would prove the second yellow card.
In this way, and since Real Madrid will as leader of his group, both players will be exactly the sanction by the next game of the liguilla, against auxerre, and they can advance clean of cards to the next stage.
Finally, the Committee of discipline of UEFA has given two games by coach Jose mourinho, and with varying amounts to the players involved.
The provocation of a yellow card in circumstances like this or similar is not a new practice, but more frequent in the world of football.
It is so widespread that form part of the ethos of the unwritten rules, but, in this sport.
Part of the debate emerged in the case mentioned it has been involved a team of the excellence of real Madrid (who in his anthem prides itself of nobility and honor, and that in the past has fined for their players for similar acts) and dramatizing orchestrated, apparently, by mourinho, who adds one more episode to its long history of technical sweeping and provocative.
In any case, the debate revolves around whether this kind of behaviour does not expressly prohibited by the regulation goes against the principles of sport, that is, if with these actions committed fraud law; for, indeed, are actions - sporting regulation, but seem to avoid.
The issue is to examine the type of damage they cause to the sporting spirit.
One of the goods that comprises the sporting spirit is the physical integrity of the players, as with these actions are not endangered, that is to say, there was no violent game.
Another of these goods that are continuing the play is to prevent the team from the players offenders is profiting unfairly the opposing team, happened.
However, the paradox of the action of the players from Real Madrid is not acomodó what normally we characterize as trap or fraud law, since its infringement of the rules are not made on to try to avoid punishment, but that his action was to be the most obvious is to receive the punishment of the referee.
They happily and accepted the punishment.
Another question is what kind of advantage gets offenders in the intentional examined.
Here it must be pointed out that it is in terms of the rival or benefiting from the same party, obviously, the result of the action it is to leave the home team with fewer players.
And it is also a useful strategy for the next game, because the club could not count on these players.
The advantage, of course, is that the players will begin the next phase of the Champions League without cards could threaten his participation in a future party.
But it is an advantage in the long term, with a certain degree of lack of precision, because the team can be eliminated the first change, and also with this performance players meet a party of penalties and converted the second cycle of cards in the suspension for accumulation of cards comes with a less than in the first round.
So, of rounds, is not so clear that it is an advantage.
In short, these actions do not militate against sporting spirit, which is part of the strategic decisions that favor to take maximum advantage of allowing the rules.
In the event that the players did not act to avoid the implementation of the sanction (this would be a clear case of fraud law), but rather when they chose to take it.
Made a strategic decision without evade punishment or flee the same.
Although the border between genius and fraud law is unclear, on this occasion I believe it was a clear case of ingenuity.
The controversy, I think, by two factors: because it was two autoexpulsiones and by the way in which it conducted the transmission of the guideline provocarlas.
The damage caused to the principles of sport by these actions is not as much ethical as aesthetic.
