China maintains goals of reducing greenhouse gases
The representative of the country in the COP16 assured that his country has made enormous efforts to reduce the carbon footprint and detailed that maintains its bid to cut to the 2020 between 40 and 45 percent its emission of greenhouse gases.
China maintains its bid to cut between 40 and 45 percent its emission of greenhouse gases by the year 2020, sealed his Wei, a representative of that country in the COP16.
In his first public appearance in the 16 conference of the parties to the UN Framework Convention on Climate Change (COP16), Su Wei assured that his country has made enormous efforts to reduce the carbon footprint and convert to their industry.
Indeed, in the past four years their country has invested $245 million in efforts to reduce emissions of greenhouse gases.
However, he made clear that China will not alter its goals, but will continue working together with the international community in this area.
Concerned that the Chinese strategy on climate change is divided into four business units: dialogue; construction of skills; construction of institutions and support to pilot programmes.
In all these items have been taken developments, including passage last year of a new energy law, which takes up goals for reducing emissions of gases, explained.
On the other hand, highlighted that in China, federal authorities have been working in concert with state and local, to achieve the goals of energy saving, energy efficiency and reduction of emissions.
Moreover, he, are in progress or already concluded various multi-annual plans, both funded by the Chinese Government, and by governments of other countries.
For example, referred, the efficient use of energy, which was enacted over the past five years, and received investments of the organization of the United Nations (UN), the government and private initiative.
It is also a provincial project of climate change, another for the return of outbreaks glow for savers and one more of mitigation and adaptation, detailed.
At the same table, Martin krol, scientific adviser to the government of this country in terms of climate change, that the efforts of China have been done to the that in general, we think.
For example, exposed, the per capita emission of greenhouse gases in China is of six tonnes per person, while in the United States is 100 tonnes; China is responsible for the 9 percent of the historic contribution in pollution.
It also has been making efforts without precedent in the use of energy, and increase by 20% energy efficiency in the past five years and plan to do so much towards the year 2020, he.
