As a precautionary measure, were evacuated two homes.
By night, there was another landslide rolling land in saint-lin-laurentides, in lanaudière.
Sank a road.
From Tuesday to Wednesday evening, various regions recorded strong rainfall, between 40 and 70 millimetres of rain.
In addition, there are between 20 and 40 additional millimetres from now until Thursday evening, depending on the region.
The sectors north of the river and in the valley of the outaouais were the worst hit.
Could receive up to a total of 100 millimetres of rain.
Given that these were joining the melting of the snow that had already been accumulated in certain sectors, there are fears that various rivers are spilling over.
On Wednesday night, the unit of civil defence of Quebec issued alerts for rivers ouareau and achigan, in lanaudière.
The rivers of the North, in saint-jérôme, laurentides, and chêne, in lotbinière, have already caused flooding in the past and are under surveillance.
