A king of kung-fu in Montreal
The montrealés of Algerian origin nacereddine zemmal has had an extremely peculiar journey.
The athlete, who excels in "sanda (" kung-fu "full contact"), kickboxing and and Thai box, to get to the tatamis and rings in the world in search of new challenges.
"I began to train in martial arts like kung-fu and kickboxing 12 years ago, in Algeria," said zemmal, who lives in the metropolis since 2008 to make progress on the professional level.
"in my case, I seek fighting everywhere because, for those who do not enjoy the game on the ground that the mixed martial arts, there are few events in North America."
The athlete, who works as a security officer and as an employee of the company UPS, recently gave bad news to their rivals, winning two gold medals at the world championship of the world amateur karate and kickboxing Association (wka), held from 23 to 30 October in Edinburgh, Scotland.
"I have won in the categories of kickboxing full contact and Thai box," he explained.
"Today I prepare to participate in the World Cup of San shou in China."
"They are the athletes who have ended up among the first four points in the last World Championship in each category."
"In 2009, I earned the bronze in Toronto."
"in 2005, in Vietnam, to finish in eighth place."
"in 2007, in China, finalicé the tournament in fifth place, but reached the third place in Toronto in 2009," he added.
"What is interesting is that I have moved forward in every competition."
"At this rate, I will be the first this time or next year!"
The "San shou" or "sanda" is an original discipline of China in the strike with his fists and feet, as well as launching opponents to the ground.
The clashes were originally held on a platform and, less frequently, in a ring.
The pugilista more famous in this kind of combat is the American of Vietnamese origin cung Le, widely recognised in the world of martial arts.
Although born zemmal just keep a race in his career, no doubt will come to the great tournament as "king of sanda," the super bowl of kung-fu.
"This competition is the most notorious and prestigious of China," explains the cutesy boy.
"It is the equivalent to the stadium lumpinee (the biggest stadium in Thailand)."
"It has been an incredible experience."
Zemmal has won his first match, in the semi-finals of their category (80 kg), but lost in the final.
"I won it is a true professional," she said.
"There are four competitors by category (80 kg, 85 kg, 90 kg and 90 kg)."
"the winners of the semi-final encounter at the end of his" category.
"then, the champions of each category face to complement to a single champion, the King of kung-fu."
450 million in contracts without tendering
Hydro-québec has granted direct contracts worth $450 million dollars to companies of engineering to the hydro-electric project eastmain-1-a-sarcelle-rupert.
In the centre of this avalanche of more than 100 contracts is a consortium of companies bpr, Dessau, sm and Groupe axor, achieved without a tender after the contract more important, the management of the project, for a sum of 295 million.
The consortium, called énergie gérance, was created in 2004 following the decision of hydro-québec to entrust the private sector their responsibility to manage this important hydro-electric project of $5 billion.
In early 2005, the consortium énergie gérance won the lucrative contract without that were previously a public tender.
For the party quebequense, resorting to groups of companies raises a serious ethical issue that threatens to eliminate competition and lead to higher prices.
"This is a new method of collusion and eliminate the competition."
"that is, the people, instead of doing so in secret, now do so openly," said yesterday the Member of the Party quebequense Sylvain simard at a press conference.
Earlier, in the morning, Mr simard raised the issue in the National Assembly, because, he says, does not understand how they can benefit the public interest in this way.
The Minister of natural resources, Nathalie normandeau, responded by the afternoon, strongly denied that there has been collusion with this contract.
"I am beginning to cansarme," objected, arguing that the PQ had acted so "dishonest" and "with a lack of rigour."
It noted that "the least" would be that the PQ is disculpase.
The formula of the trusts is a common practice in the world.
Normally, this is an alliance with a time limit which allows two or more companies bringing their expertise to answer a tender for a complex project.
The project eastmain presents a high level of complexity, bearing in mind the magnitude of the works.
Work has already begun and durarán until 2012.
Throughout the case, the contract was awarded without that came in game competition; it has been a negotiation.
In addition, the formulation of groups has ceased to be the exception to the norm in Quebec, even for relatively simple projects.
As posted last week Le Devoir, the formula of the pools in the area of technical advice is being subjected to an investigation into the government.
A quick glance at the commercial register of Quebec to identify more than 200 pools, some of which appear to be permanent.
In this way, the company Dessau is working in partnership with the majority of its competitors, such as top +, génivar, snc-lavalin, Roche et tecsult, and others.
Each combination, and there are dozens of them, leads to a single legal entity, namely Dessau.
With regard to the consortium énergie gérance, Minister normandeau has stressed that "the territory of James Bay responds to a dynamic of labour particular and hydro-québec responds specifically to it from the years 1970."
The head of the project eastmain, réal laporte, of the Société d 'énergie of the Baie James (sebj), has given an explanation that has highlighted the fact that the contract of management of the project has been granted directly.
"If respondes for a tender and there are few participants, your prices will be higher."
"You have two options: you can come into contact with the industry and say: we will negotiate a satisfactory agreement and with a good price."
"however, the idea is that what matters is not the price, but the power of the people," said Mr laporte.
The contract granted to the consortium énergie gérance form part of a long list of contracts of more than $50,000 obtained by the party quebequense.
The contracts were granted by hydro-québec or the sebj for the project eastmain-1-a-sarcelle-rupert.
After checking, Le Devoir has identified 109 contracts of technical advice provided between 2002 and March 2010 to companies and their subsidiaries, in particular geotécnicos laboratories.
Snc-lavalin has won 22 contracts, génivar managed 16, 14 and 10 tecsult Dessau, without taking into account their participation in énergie gérance.
All the contracts were negotiated.
In total, amount to 449.783.344 dollars, including the contract of énergie gérance of 295.131.564 dollars.
Sylvain simard has hinted that the four companies that form the consortium (bpr, Dessau, sm and Groupe axor) are "good acquaintances of the Liberal Party of Quebec."
The Minister normandeau has dropped the PQ is also linked to these companies, "funded," before explaining that it is rather more of their leaders.
A barometer of the responsible consumption. The label 'green' does not inspire confidence.
Greener, but deeply cynical.
The consumer quebequense little confidence in the global sustainable development, as well as in trademarks of fair trade and ecological certificates to guide their elections.
According to the barometer of the responsible consumption, whose first results were published yesterday, the situation is even worse. The consumer is submerged in a media universe for messages in support of a more responsible consumption, but regrets the lack of reliable information and considers it even slams his commitment.
Even if it has increased the consumption of products called "socially responsible" in 2010, the natives of Quebec should appear to give little credence to those trying to sell them.
Two thirds of them say, in fact, they do not trust the environmental commitment of companies or in advertising environmentalists, reveals the measurement tool developed by the centre of the responsible consumption of the University of sherbrooke.
Another conclusion: half of consumers casts doubt on the reliability of the official certificates that carry products called fair, as well as the credibility of products and brands that have labels indicating that are "ecorresponsables," says the barometer.
Similarly, only 14.6% of the natives of Quebec should seriously speeches of politicians on this issue.
In any case, the information on the responsible consumption appears essential to stimulating this sector of consumption, fuelled today by nearly a third of the natives of Quebec should consumers.
In fact, the gaps and the dubious nature of the information make a 46% of consumers endeavouring this option.
It is the second obstacle is identified by the barometer, after the higher price of these products.
Moreover, a third of the natives of Quebec should say also distrust of the supposed Returns of products or environmental services that they are trying to sell.
Moreover, almost half of consumers changed their habits in 2010 and, especially, changed the brand of one or several products to comply with their beliefs.
A 61% has given priority to purchases in shops in his neighborhood and preferred to buy food grown in the region, says the barometer.
Greener and responsible (the rate of responsible consumption has reached 64 points on a maximum of 100 this year), Homo consumus of Quebec loves taking the place of the King of recycling that tries to reduce its impact on the environment for the protection of wildlife.
However, according to the barometer, this social conscience seems to be of doors (her car) outside: in 2010, only 28% of the natives of Quebec should indicated that used public transport or have shared car to defend his environmental principles.
In addition, the 39,1% of the participants of this comprehensive survey of behaviour, which has just completed its first edition, supports the use of cycling and walking.
A loan so that the state has excentris
The government of Quebec, which have been asked to commit financially in the recovery of the complex of cinemas excentris pursuit the Société Angus and the parallèle, agrees, but only through a loan.
The Société de Développement Angus and the parallèle, who expected a donation of seven billion dollars in the Ministry of Culture to come back to buy Daniel langlois the complex excentris film on the Boulevard saint-laurent and restore it to its true cinéfila, have not got everything they asked for.
The government has agreed to become involved in the matter, but in its own terms.
Instead of the expected donation, the government of Quebec proposes a loan whose value would be, in fact, short of initial expectations, it could be a viable solution in favourable conditions, at least in the opinion of certain public employees.
Quebec had already rejected last spring, a first action plan and an application of 12.8 billion, but since then, the requests have been revised downwards.
The President of the Société de Développement des Entreprises culturelles (sodec), François macerola, who leads the dossier of excentris, sent a proposal and an action plan to the Minister st-pierre.
He has presented a new report about ten days ago.
However, the sodec received a counter-proposal from the cabinet on Tuesday.
The parallèle and Angus have until 31 December to respond to the same.
In any case, it seems that it must be phased out completely the hypothesis of a donation from the state.
Let us remember that the association of owners of cinemas and cinematic complex in Quebec is opposed to a direct investment from the state to support the recovery of excentris, arguing that the Ministry of Culture should not finance building projects, as it has done with other cinemas.
On the other hand, various industry representatives did claim a considerable economic aid.
Daniel langlois, the owner of the same, has been for ten years the burden of copyright in their local cinema complex, after finance its own construction, which could justify a derogation from the Council of the Treasury.
The lack of rooms for independent films is evident in Montreal and excentris had managed to entice custom.
The company Angus and the parallèle, led by Christian yaccarini, for its part of a campaign financing in private, hoping to raise $700,000 for their way towards the acquisition.
Since the spring of 2009, only one of these rooms, the parallèle, still casts films in excentris.
The aim of future buyers is reopening the three rooms next February 27, sending the precious film of Xavier beauvois "des hommes et des centre."
However, Christian yaccarini has again been in contact with Le Devoir and we do not know what they think he and his group of the proposals that have been given.
