"The Secretary agreed to review the case."
Finally, we can mention that have warmed, the mood in connection with the website WikiLeaks.
Tom flanagan, a former assistant to very close to Stephen Harper, said in the CBC radio that the responsible for this massive should be "shot."
In America they echo of Mike Huckabee.
A global plan to renew the lighting
Yesterday, the UN has proposed in Cancun a plan for the renovation of the lighting domestic, commercial and industrial in 100 countries to reduce greenhouse gases (GHGs) in an amount that is almost a third of the additional reduction that must be carried out to stabilise the climate of the planet before 2020.
This ambitious plan is enshrined in all major projects that the UN expected to be adopted in Cancún to compensate for the lack of binding commitments of reduction in industrialised countries.
According to the plan put forward yesterday, if the incandescent light bulbs, who still hold between 50 and 70% of the market, it sustituyesen with fluocompactas or, even better, with of electroluminescentes diodes (or "thing" in English), we do not have much of the 1.8 million tonnes (GT) of GHGs issued on the planet to enlighten humans.
Lighting accounts for 8% of global emissions.
It is the equivalent to 70% of the emissions of the cars planetary.
In Copenhagen, the last year, the largest emitters, such as the United States, China, Europe and others, including Canada, committed themselves to a voluntary reduction to reduce global emissions of GHGs from 53 GT to 49 GT.
However, should be lessened even 5 GT of that sum to stabilize before 2020, rising temperatures to two degrees Celsius to avoid get out of control.
In the incandescent light bulbs, 95% of the energy is settling in the form of heat and the remaining 5%, produces light.
In the case of the fluocompactas light bulbs, energy expenditure is reduced by 75% and with the new bulbs LEDs, is still two times more energy consumption.
Light bulbs fluocompactas lasts an average of between 6,000 and 10,000 hours.
The new LED bulbs, such as those that has launched the manufacturer Philips this week (a company which, moreover, has been involved in the study by the UN), have a life expectancy of 25,000 hours and consume 80% less energy than an incandescent light bulb, which enables us to have an idea of the savings you get with the substitution plan to apply in 100 countries.
These new bulbs can also work with reóstatos and emit very little heat.
Above, contain nothing of mercury.
Various specialists have expressed reservations in relation to the fluocompactas bulbs, because they contain mercury, and that must be eliminated as hazardous waste, which is not always possible in the developing countries, except that manufacturers affix instructions.
However, the report stated, the main source of mercury emissions in the world are not fluocompactas bulbs, but the coal-fired power plants, which emit a lot of mercury to produce the electricity is wasted with incandescent light bulbs.
Only in the United States, these plants emit 25,000 tonnes of mercury each year.
The report details the benefits that will provide this programme for each country.
For example, Indonesia would save it $1 billion a year in electricity and eight million tonnes of CO2 - equivalent to 3.5 coal-fired power stations which would cost $2.5 million.
Ivory Coast hopes very much the announcement of the election results
The UN Secretary General, Ban Ki-moon, has demanded the "immediate release" of the results of the presidential election in the Ivory Coast, given that have slipped the deadlines.
"The Secretary-General highlighted the need for the Independent Electoral Commission to complete its work and announced the interim results immediately," highlights a mouthpiece for the head of the UN.
'calls on the parties of Ivory Coast and institutions to demonstrate their sense of responsibility and refrain from any initiative to which advertised the provisional results. "
Despite pressure from some foreign governments, the electoral commission has left the deadline of Wednesday at midnight without released the results three days since the elections on Sunday.
Around 40 minutes before the deadline, the President of the CIS had commented on television that the Commission was working "to announce the results.
The Wednesday have multiplied in the world calls for the CIS then finally the name of the winner of the runoff between the outgoing Laurent Gbagbo, and Alassane Ouattara his opponent.
However, the side took account with the annulment by the Constitutional Council "fraudulent" in the North, in the hands of the ex-rebellion forces of new (national) from the failed coup of September 2002.
Pascal affi N " guessan, director of the campaign, the President of Ivory Coast, has said that the manoeuvres of intimidation of voters conducted for the National Front in the north of the country had deterred followers of the outgoing President to go to vote.
All the election could be cancelled if the Constitutional Council accepts complaints lodged by Gbagbo.
However, opponents of Gbagbo see the highest court in the country is not neutral, since it is directed by Paul Yao N dré, a close political ally of Gbagbo.
Alassane Ouattara, a man from the north that belies any relationship with the former rebels, has tried to "unacceptable" the delay in the publication of the results and has asked Gbagbo to them, but has not gone so far as to claim victory.
Its allies claim that Gbagbo is blocking the publication of the results because he knows that they have lost and to submit a complaint to the Constitutional Council having prevented the Electoral Commission the dissemination of the results, it would be illegal.
The second round of the presidential, on Sunday, should have put the icing on the process of reunification and reconciliation of a country divided in two years.
The United Nations has warned Wednesday to the political class of Ivory Coast that could be liable for possible violence.
Laurent Gbagbo had ended up in the first round, on 31 October, with 38% of the votes compared to 32% of Alassane Ouattara, which received the support of the former President, Henri Konan Bédié (25% in the first round).
The unemployment rate remains stable in France in the third quarter
According to the International Labour Organisation (ILO), the rate of unemployment in France has remained stable at 9.3% in mainland (9.7% in view of the overseas departments), as the data corrected for seasonal variations (cve) temporary released on Thursday by the insee.
The number of unemployed is left in 2.631.000 in mainland France.
Data from the second quarter have been confirmed, a 9.3% of the workforce in mainland and 9.7% with the Dom.
In a year, the unemployment rate has been an increase of 0.1 points.
In general, 3.4 million people in metropolitan France represented not worked in the third quarter, but want to work, whether or not they are available in the two weeks of work and seeking employment or not.
The situation of young people in the labour market has continued to decline, with a further increase in the unemployment rate up to 24.2% in mainland France (+ 0.9 points in three months, + 0.5 points in a year), 25% including the French overseas departments.
During the third quarter, 637.000 young people aged between 15 and 24 were unemployed in the sense of the ILO.
For his part, there has been a slight increase in unemployment among older people, until the 6.4% in mainland France (+ 0.2 points in three months and a year), that is to say, 482.000 people of more than 50 years, a figure that amounts to 6.6% in the French overseas departments.
Only recorded a stability of unemployment among people aged between 25 and 49 years, with an 8.3 percent in mainland France (-0,1 points in three months, + 0.1 points in a year) and 8.8% across France.
The insee leads since 2006 without publish the monthly unemployment rate, after a controversy over their methods of calculation.
Eurostat, the statistical agency of the European Union, it is still doing so and announced on Tuesday a rate of 9.8% for France (DOM including) in October, after a 9.9% in September.
Alexander guérini investigated and arrested
Alexander guérini, 53, senior manager of business waste and brother of President PS General Council Bouches-du-Rhône, is being investigated and has been imprisoned in the prison of luynes, near aix-en-provence, in the context of an investigation into contracts allegedly fraudulent.
Alexander guérini is being investigated for abuse of goods, diversion of funds and public property, cover-up, active corruption, and possession of ammunition, according to indicates his lawyer.
"Alexander guérini will fight and will answer all the questions which you raise the magistrate, no ghosts."
"It is easy to follow you for a multitude of reprehensible acts and demonstrate this," he told the AFP her lawyer, Florence rault, before the hearing his client.
Mr guérini, brother of the leader of the Socialist Party in the department, jean-noël guérini, has wanted to convey through their lawyers to the judge before his hearing, a document to be explained.
On Wednesday night began to investigate and also explains to one of their people close, Philippe rapezzi.
According to his lawyer, Mr lucien Simon, all he has done his client has been dealing with the waste that must be managed.
As regards the allocation of contracts or the fate of the funds relating to his execution, he does not know anything about it, says Mr Simon.
In the context of this dossier, is also being investigated since Wednesday Daniel pinna, former Director General of the services of the urban agglomeration of aubagne, for embezzlement and complicity, but he has left in parole and has prevented from meeting with the players in the case.
"My client has been able to explain all the facts that have reproached."
"the investigating magistrate has taken account of the explanations and he has made in freedom," said his lawyer, Mr Yann arnoux.
On Tuesday evening to Wednesday interrogaron four others and left the freedom, under judicial control in the case of two of them, as has been said by the deputy prosecutor of the Republic, Michel raffin.
Michel karabadjakian, deputy director general of the ownership of Marseille métropole Provence (mpm), has been accused by "influence and passive corruption."
Two officials of the crowding of aubagne, Michèle duval and Christophe bringuier, have been questioned by "theft and misuse of public goods by someone dedicated to public service" and "complicity in the embezzlement of public funds," respectively.
Finally, the companion of Alexander guérini, jeannie peretti, is being investigated for "cover-up of the misuse of social goods."
Among people who have been opposed to Mr guérini says Stéphane brunengo-girard, jailed recently in a parallel case procurement fraud cases involving Corsica.
The researchers suspect that their societies have to launder capital of major crime.
The investigation is underway in the framework of various legal instructions started against X in April 2009 following the receipt of an anonymous communications, for alleged fraud in the allocation of public contracts, particularly in the field of waste.
A source close to the investigation says that the investigations are concentrating especially on the conditions of allocation and operation of a landfill in La ciotat, which includes the wastes of aubagne, as well as other cities of the urban community of Marseille (mpm).
Subject Clotilde Reiss: the Élysée Palace has exaggerated the mediation of Syria
For more than ten months, between July 2009 and May 2010, the fate of Clotilde Reiss, a young French researcher, was detained in Iran for "spying," has been in thrall to the public in France, has alerted diplomacy and deepening the deterioration of relations between Paris and Tehran.
All under the watchful eye of diplomats from the United States.
The American documents obtained by WikiLeaks and consulted by Le Monde reveal some unknown aspects of this crisis.
Painting the Élysée Palace has explained its strategy for the Americans to the point of advise them to manage their own crisis of "hostages" in Iran (a small group of senderistas).
Show how French officials trying to persuade Washington that the release of a young French woman not occurred in exchange for the release of Majid kakavand, an Iranian arrested in France and wanted by the US justice for trafficking of materials for the Iranian nuclear program.
Finally, show the harsh reality of how the French Presidency tried to manipulate the media to give the idea that the Syrian President, Bashar al-Assad, had played a key role in the release of Clotilde Reiss.
In fact, did nothing.
A diplomatic telegram drafted on 12 August 2009 in Paris bears the title "Iran: French comments on how to manage cases of hostage taking."
The Élysée Minister for strategic affairs, François richier, accompanied by the director of the Quai d " orsay to Northern Africa and the Middle East, Patrice paoli, conversan with the American diplomatic allegrone Kathleen.
He explained the French method.
Advise Americans to do the following to repatriate their own citizens detained in force in Iran.
"What noise," they say, "soltad continuously" in the media the words "fundamental human rights," "innocence," "immediate release."
All to shame the Iranian regime, careful of his image.
"When you ask Iranians paréis, hacedlo more often still."
Because, once exhausted attempts at negotiation remained channels, "the silence will not solve anything," the Iranians are "delaying tactics."
Mr richier adds that the detention of foreigners is "an Iranian tactic: the taking of hostages for political blackmail."
Announcing the release from prison of Clotilde Reiss (which will happen on 16 August day when they are hiding in the French embassy) "will require the players to the Iranians of a large amount of money" (230 euros of reward).
In addition, the Élysée Palace foreshadows other hostage crisis, a phenomenon that will increase ."
The Iranians could "in the near future to arrest one of the nearly 1,800 French citizens who live in Iran," she says.
28 August 2009.
Clotilde Reiss released from prison after 12 days, but it is blocked in Iran.
It conveys the following information: the Iranian kakavand Majid, whose extradition by the United States for illicit trafficking of electronic material sensitive towards Iran, has been released in Paris by decision of a judge.
The American embassy, like many observers, doubt this strange coincidence.
For Washington, which close the criminal networks Iranians of procurement for the nuclear programme, the release of Majid khakavand is bad news.
How has accepted France an exchange?
Will release of Iran in exchange for the French?
For a new conversation with Kathleen allegrone, on 4 September, François richier ensures that did not happen.
The Élysée Palace, says, "not only are too was surprised by the decision of the judge," but that has been trying to oppose it.
"There has been intense negotiations between the French Presidency and the Minister of Justice" (at the time, Michèle Alliot-Marie), but "the French Government cannot overturn the decision," he says.
Mr richier also wants to demonstrate that Majid kakavand remains under "close observation" of the information services.
The Élysée adviser at a telephone number, hanging and, later, reported to us that the Iranian diplomat, "is currently at a Paris managed by the Iranian embassy."
During the detention of Clotilde Reiss in Iran, the Élysée Palace does not mince its efforts, uses communiqués and leaks in the media to believe that the Syrian President Bashar al-Assad is a "very important" and "influential" of "mediator."
Americans are watching this activity with some irony and see which brings its fruits, as several press articles sent the French official version.
A telegram dated 25 August 2009 mentions "'blitz' media coverage of French officials."
What must such "thanks" towards Mr Assad, asks the embassy in Paris.
"in spite of their declarations of praise, French officials privately admit that only have a vague idea of what they have really done the Syrians'.
Then, the document is the reasons that have led to the Élysée Palace to produce this fiction.
The great effort "aims to strengthen the policy of Sarkozy of opening to Syria," she said.
A policy that began in 2008, which "in the view of many critics in France and abroad, just as premature and desmerecida."
The "exaggerating the Syrian role," Paris is trying to "show Syria the praise they can reap if it plays a constructive role in the region."
The goal also is to "sow the seeds of discord between Syria and Iran."
The US embassy knows from good source.
On 11 August, François richier entrusted: "of course, we do not know if the Syrians have done something, or not."
"But anyway, we were grateful."
"at least, this should lead to confusion between the Iranians."
Clotilde Reiss returns to France on 16 May of 2010.
Nicolas Sarkozy receives in the Élysée Palace.
In a statement, thanks to the Presidents of Brazil, Senegal and Syrian played an "active role in favour of the release of our fellow."
From midnight, the young Koreans cannot play online
The South Korean government is going to adopt a law called "Cinderella" that will prevent teenagers participating in online games after midnight to block their access, according to government officials have indicated.
In December, will be submitted a draft law to Parliament to ask companies online games that block access to these Games after midnight to young people of less than 16 years, according to said representatives from the Ministries of culture and family.
"many children play all night and, later, it is difficult to study in school and lead a normal life during the day."
"We think that this law is needed to protect their health and their right to dream," declared the AFP Jo Rhine, ministerial responsibility for the bill.
Online gambling will be available again at six in the morning.
Companies will have a year to prepare for the implementation of the law, accurate.
The government is also asking companies to limit the time of daily access to these Games when the parents of the young request, added the officer.
Furthermore, will provide who request free computer programs that can limit the time to connect to the Internet.
South Korea is one of the countries most "connected" and newspapers report news regularly on various facts associated with intensive use of the Internet.
The country is also the undisputed champion of the world events online games.
In November, South Korea won four gold medals at the world cyber games, where she faced other 58 countries.
2018-2022 world: FIFA appoints the organising countries
In the middle of the storm caused by suspicions of corruption, the Executive Committee of FIFA termed the Thursday to the organisers of the world cups of 2018 and 2022, a clear policy where the struggles of influence and the lobbying may take precedence over the technical criteria.
One thing is clear, the 2018 FIFA competition will be held in Europe, traditional stronghold of the discipline (four candidates: England, Russia, españa-portugal and countries bajos-bélgica).
The edition of 2022 will be much more exotic, given that the International Federation hopes to conquer new territories (Qatar, Australia), after a premiere in the African continent in 2010, or continue with its introduction in the United States or in the Far East (Japan, South Korea).
The list of those persons who were part of the delegations (David Cameron, Prince William, José Luis Rodríguez Zapatero, José Socrates, Bill Clinton, the Emir of Qatar, the Heads of Government of the Belgian and Dutch, Zidane and Beckham, Cruyff) testifies to the political and economic interests at stake in a World Cup.
The transactions in the wings, therefore, it is possible that will last until the last minute.
Furthermore, it is difficult to establish a hierarchy between the candidates.
According to the evaluation report of FIFA, the English, Portuguese (2018) and American (2022) have better arguments that their competitors.
However, these considerations do not have much weight to the 22 members of the Executive Committee at the time of the vote.
The Sunday Times, responsible for the revelations that led to the suspension by corruption of two members of the EC (reynald temarii and Amos Adamu), could have ruined so the chances of his country, cradle of football, that only hosted the World Cup once in 1966.
The BBC added fuel to the fire on Monday by releasing a documentary that was to three influential Members of the EC, Ricardo Teixeira, Nicolas leoz and Issa hayatou.
Enough to upsetting FIFA and shaming those responsible English, that have embarked on an intense lobbying in recent weeks, with David Cameron at the helm.
The head of government hopes the coup when squabbles with success by his predecessor, Tony Blair, who had succeeded in 2005 to London the organisation of the jj.oo. 2012.
This intense activity, will it be enough to restore the luster of England before the EC?
It is not clear, given that the duo españa-portugal consideration with many strengths thanks to their stadiums, ready to go, his experience (world of 82 in Spain, jj.oo in Barcelona in 1992, European Cup in 2004 in Portugal) and his footballing culture.
However, the gloomy economic outlook and financial both countries could break down their ambitions.
The possible reprisals against the English and the doubts about the solvency of Spain and Portugal all you do is give points to Russia, which became an outsider in weight despite the gaps in his candidacy (stadiums, hotels, transport).
However, Prime Minister Vladimir Putin decided not to travel to Zurich and has denounced a "unfair competition in the preparation of the vote," in a direct reference to the allegations of the English press against members of the EC.
"They are drawing up their skeletons, trying to involve them pro-actively," said Putin.
By 2022, the United States, which have the experience of 1994, appear to be the most logical favourite.
First world economic power and headquarters of the main sponsors of FIFA, the country seems to require advantage to Japan and South Korea, which have developed separately an excellent project.
However, these new candidates seem premature to two countries that have organised together the championship in 2002.
