In addition to Qatar, which submitted its plan in futuristic stadiums, and Australia, FIFA have no with its expansion into new horizons, but both countries present more risks than certainties.
Australia, like Japan and Korea, also could be hampered by the weakness of the rights of TV paid (depending on the time difference) by European countries, the backbone of the war to FIFA.
