"always lifeline that can win," corrects Alain Juppé, resigned before the evidence.
The euro: the ECB is obliged to maintain its purchases of government bills
The last meeting of the Board of Governors of the European Central Bank (ECB) of the year should allow working out the modalities of exit from the crisis, or at least, to announce the shutdown of a large number of operations of unconventional monetary policy that they should be completed at the end of the year.
Because of the crisis of the European sovereign debt, the Institute of emission of Frankfurt certainly cannot afford to be so imperative if does not want to risk aggravating a situation more difficult today in the European bond markets.
The political price would be just as high.
Yesterday, during a press conference, the French Finance Minister, Christine Lagarde, has backed the active role played by the ECB in favour of the solution to the debt crisis of the European States.
Unwilling to say whether he thought that the Central Bank should do more, by for example its programme of purchases of government bonds.
"I reserve my opinion to my fellow Europeans'...
The eve, in Brussels, during his hearing before the Committee on Economic and Monetary Affairs of the European Parliament, the President of the ECB, Jean-Claude Trichet, there was more eloquent regarding their intentions, adding only that the programme of buying government bonds in the secondary market "remained" and that "we will see what we decided" during the meeting on Thursday.
The only thing that is clear is that the ECB will keep its main rate unchanged at 1%, the lowest level in its history since May 2009.
In practice, the purchase of Treasury bonds by the ECB has doubled in the past week to about 1.35 billion euros.
In addition, according to the indiscretos market operators, yesterday would have bought again titles in Ireland and Portugal.
In total, the central banks of the Eurosystem have acquired titles for an amount of approximately 67,000 million euros from May 2010.
Between market operators, not the slightest doubt that they purchases (consult page 29).
Economists also expect any significant changes of direction.
Although the loans to more than three months have already disappeared in the arsenal of the ECB, it still makes appropriations unlimited liquidity conditions beneficial and predictable that vary between one week and three months.
Economists expect today to be extended this provision for some months.
"I imagine it will modify its program."
"If not, ran the risk of causing the new tensions in the short term," she said Michael schubert, an economist at Commerzbank.
"It seems more likely that there will be a gradual exit announced during the first quarter of 2011," anticipates by Norbert bräms, an economist in salt.
Oppenheim.
With regard to interventions in the market of public debt, "the ECB should maintain a volume of purchase of those obligations to which the market remains stable," adds Norbert bräms.
Bearing in mind the importance of the exhibitions of European banks to the markets of sovereign debts of the euro zone, the Institute of emission has no choice but to maintain their presence in the market.
"must compensate any price the lack of investors in the market and to ensure that prevent a sharp rise in yields subscribers for the States most vulnerable," was yesterday a major operator of obligations.
Because, if interest rates are sky-high, States will have even more problems for reducing its debt, or even to stabilizing.
This is the price of protecting the euro.
In Italy, the government of Berlusconi weathers the Storm
After that it started the week with a disturbing, the situation improved slightly yesterday with the decline of the types of obligations to 10 years.
A recovery of the precarious calm.
On the way out of a meeting with the Minister of economy, the regional Presidents have argued that listened to Giulio Tremonti describe the situation of "unfathomable" and that it hoped a weekend "unpredictable," statements contradicted later by the individual.
In any event, on Tuesday the difference with long-term rates Germans had reached a record of 210 basis points and the price of the contracts of hedging against the risk of default (crq) had skyrocketed to 263 points, causing a stir in Rome.
In the Council of Ministers, Silvio Berlusconi commented that, in Spain, the difference with the Germans was greater than 400 basis points.
But his right arm, Gianni Letta, was "deeply concerned" over "the turbulence in the markets" and by contagion from Ireland.
"The good news is that Italy, the third-largest economy in the euro zone, is not as Greece or Ireland."
"The bad news is that it is as Portugal," says Irwin stelzer, an economist at the Hudson Institute.
In reality, the problem is the lack of growth and the stagnation of the revenue associated with the same, which means that the State run the risk of not being able to meet its funding needs.
The latest forecasts in Brussels have dealt a heavy blow to the government.
It is estimated that the Italian growth will reach 1.1% in 2011 and 1.4% in 2012, while the budget that is being debated in the Senate is based on figures from 1.3% and 2%, respectively.
In these conditions, according to the European Commission, the public deficit would represent the 4.3% of GDP next year (compared to 3.9% predicted by the government) and 3.5% in 2012 (instead of 2.7%).
Hence the suggestion that can be applied new budgetary arrangements after the holidays, for an amount of EUR 7 billion.
"If necessary, should be adopted new austerity measures," does the Commissioner for Economic Affairs, Olli Rehn.
For the moment, Italy has the support of the international institutions.
"The foundations of the economy are in order and its accounts in good condition, as we have been saying for a long time ago," arrigo sadun, the Italian manager in the International Monetary Fund responsible for Italy in the IMF.
"There is no immediate problem, short-term or long-term, because despite its considerable debt (119,2% of GDP in 2011,], the stabilization efforts requested by Italy are lower than those required of other countries," says Pier Carlo padoan, chief economist of the OECD.
Is the problem of political instability.
On 14 December, Silvio Berlusconi will face a no-confidence motion in the House of Deputies, behind which could anticipate the elections at the end of March.
In this case, it would open a little for decision-making in the event of a serious crisis.
The Europeans are thinking about strengthening the mechanisms to combat the crisis.
Christine Lagarde has already said yesterday during a press conference in Paris: "I believe that we have already shown on Sunday evening and by the day, that Europeans are clearly showing solidarity, determined, committed to the defence of its currency and its currency area."
Although he was on the decline seen yesterday in the types of the obligations of the European States prompted governments and the ECB.
However, we cannot speak of a principle of standardisation.
The rating agency Standard & Poor " s announced that could lower the rating of Portugal, the more frequent today of speculation.
"like in May, really lack clarity and transparency policies, which weighs significantly on banking systems," believe economists from exane BNP Paribas.
Especially because "the pace is far slower than the pace of the market."
Aware of this gap and of the dangers lurking, European countries intensify discussions to strengthen the mechanisms of exit from the crisis already in existence.
The informal consultations between the ministers of finance that are most directly affected and, in general, with their counterparts from the G-20 are on track.
And this also taking into account the meetings of the Eurogroup and Ecofin in early next week.
The ECB is meeting today.
In the order of the day, the kind of unconventional measures to support the countries of the euro zone in the colimador markets (look up the road).
As regards the EDF financial stability (EFSF), its chief executive, Klaus Regling, started on Tuesday in Singapore travels through Asia to inform investors of the Far East on the developments of the crisis in Europe.
Although the aim of these visits is not to raise funds, certainly preparing the ground.
It is predicted that the initial emissions of titles of the EFSF must be introduced next month.
Yesterday, a US official has entrusted to Reuters news agency that the United States would support a potential increase of the funds mobilised by an additional direct involvement of the IMF.
With regard to the countries that are first in line, Portugal and Spain, they are preparing to adopt structural reforms, particularly in relation to the organisation of the labour market.
These reforms will only add to the austerity measures with an effect closer.
Lisbon and Madrid want to move in a different way to that followed in Greece and Ireland.
Both want to avoid at all costs seek international assistance before applying their own budgetary corrections and decide the structural reforms that they consider essential to increase the confidence of a lasting.
The European funds, finally, there are options available to speed up the process of normalisation of the markets of public duties.
In passing through Paris, November 24, Axel Weber was the first to launch the idea that, if the EUR 750 million mobilised by Europe and the International Monetary Fund were not enough, the Union would not hesitate to trot out the portfolio.
Economists at Barclays Capital, a front-line player in the market of the European public debt, consider that an amount of around EUR 100 million extra would be sufficient, "preferably" in the form of direct injection of liquidity.
There is the instrument for this: the European financial stabilisation mechanism which today with 60 million euros.
A Council which, without doubt, could examine in detail the European capitals.
Especially if market conditions worsen.
Snow and ice: 24 departments on Orange alert
The snow is still causing difficulties of movement, especially in the secondary network in Britain, and can affect various economic activities.
Currently, twenty-four departments are on alert Orange because of the risk of snow and ice training.
Eure, eure-et-loir, Les Deux-Sèvres Vienne and have joined the two departments that were already on alert, 18 from Wednesday to half a day and two, dordogne and Gironde, joined the Group for the night.
According to France météo, the heavy snow falls affect North of Gironde and Charente, although snow also slightly in island of France.
We expect to see layers of snow of between 2 and 5 cm, promptly of between 7 and 10 cm, in the departments concerned, and between 1 and 3 cm, or even to 5 cm, in the Paris region.
The departments concerned are Charente, as well as Charente-Maritime, côtes d 'armor, Finistère, Gironde, dordogne Poitou, and of the regions of Lower Normandy, Ile-de-France and lemosín.
The snowfall are sufficiently robust to cause difficulties of movement and affect some economic activities, alert météo France.
In the côtes d 'armor, has banned access to a number of minor roads to heavy goods vehicles of more than 7.5 tonnes, including axes guingamp-lannion and saint-brieuc-loudéac.
According to the marshals, the movement in the secondary network of Britain is complicated, and recommend that no lead was safe in case of need and banned the movement of certain vehicles TERs during the day.
During the Thursday, has been banned at the school transport in Picardy.
There was no specific measure on Wednesday night to limit the movement of heavy vehicles.
The Prefecture "urges all drivers to lead with the utmost caution on the roads and to adapt their driving to the situation."
The Directorate General of civil aviation (dgac) asked the airlines that anulasen Thursday 25% of its flights at the Paris airport Roissy and 10% in orly because of the snow.
The dgac recommends to air passengers that are put in touch with their airline.
In Britain, Gatwick airport, south of London, and Edinburgh, in Scotland, are closed until Thursday morning.
One of the grand Paris: financial early drafts
Since the debate on the modernisation of transport on the island of France has reached its climax, raining down billions.
At least, in the debate.
In particular, we speak of the 23 million for the metro, the grand Paris that must build the Société du Grand Paris.
To initiate this GSP, the state has announced a fund of EUR 400 million.
In theory, this sum that will allow then to the GSP borrowing in the markets for part of his double loop.
Today, at last, we have the first bills.
The finance letter from 2010, examined in the Finance Committee of the National Assembly this morning, contains the devices intended to find the first part of that money.
There are two ways: the creation of a special tax of equipment and the increase in the tax offices in the island of France.
The first, as we read in Article 15 of the text of the draft law, is "in the interest of public institution Société du Grand Paris."
In addition, is set in numbers: "the product of this tax is of 117 million euros a year."
The second is a modification of the offices that already exists "to modernise, increase their product and make this increase to the Société du Grand Paris."
How much would be achieved with this method?
Who knows.
In the text does not give figures.
But it is far from 4 million.
"What is needed is that tax revenues are added to the EUR 400 million of the allocation of funds which will mobilise the state and that will be granted to the Société du Grand Paris as the project advances," you can read in the explanatory statement.
The GSP not surprised this system.
"When you create revenue (the two taxes], we can cover the studies for three years and then get the 4 million later, according to make sense of."
"We will in the budget and will be used as needed."
The GSP estimates that empecerá to receive the 4 million in 2013 for the budget of 2014.
This arrangement, in which the 4 million promised on credit, can lead to a parliamentary debate slightly firebrand.
The first public meeting will be on 7 December.
But hackers and spies diligent
The subject Wikileaks has a dual value.
On the one hand, uncovered an apparent scandal, a scandal that only seems scandal to the hypocrisy governing relations between the Member States, citizens and the press.
On the other hand, announces profound changes at international level and provides for a future dominated by the regression.
But go step by step.
The first aspect of WikiLeaks is confirmation of the fact that each case created by a secret service (regardless of the nation which appertains) consists entirely of cuts in the press.
The "extraordinary" American revelations about the sexual habits of Berlusconi only reflect what has been written for months in any newspaper (except those that belong to Berlusconi) and the profile siniestramente ridiculizador of Khadafi has for a long time giving ideas to the cabaret artists to create their sketches.
The rule whereby the secret files just must be trained by news public knowledge is essential to the dynamic of the secret services, and not just in this century.
If you visit a bookshop dedicated to publications esoteric, you will find that each work repeated (on the grail, the mystery of rennes-le-château, the templarios or the rosacruz) exactly what was written in the earlier works.
This is not due solely to the authors of ocultistas texts do not want to do new research (or does not know where to look for an update on the non-existent), but because those engaged in ocultismo not just rely on what you know, what reconfirmed that had already learned.
This is the mechanism of the success of Dan Brown.
The same applies to the secret files.
The rapporteur is perezoso, as is perezoso (or has little desire) the head of the secret services (if it could be, I know, editor of the Libération), which only considers true what can recognize.
The top secret information on Berlusconi that took the American Embassy in Rome at the State Department was the same that posted the Newsweek the previous week.
So why have caused such a stir revelations of these cases?
On the one hand, just say what all cultivated person already knows, namely that the embassies, at least since the Second World War and the Heads of States can be called by telephone or take the plane to meet for dinner, have lost his diplomatic role and, with the exception of some exercises limited representation, have been transformed into centres of spying.
Any viewer watching films of research knows perfectly well, just aparentamos that we do not know for hypocrisy.
In any case, the fact repeat publicly infringes the duty of hypocrisy and gives a bad image of American diplomacy.
Secondly, the idea that a hacker anyone can check the secrets more secrets of the world 's most powerful country significantly affects the reputation of the Department of State.
Therefore, the scandal is affecting both the victims and the "butchers."
But enter the true nature of what has happened.
It used to, in the era of Orwell, could be designed to power as a big brother who controlled every gesture of his subjects.
The prophecy of Orwell has become reality from which it can monitor every move by phone, each transaction conducted, hotel visited, motorway taken, the citizen will make this way on a complete victim of eye of power.
But when it is proven, as happens now, even the were the secrets of power cannot escape the control of a hacker, the relationship of control will be one-way and becomes circular.
The power controls to each citizen, each citizen but (at least the hacker, chosen as the vengeful of citizens) can access all the secrets of power.
How can aguantarse power that can no longer or retain their own secrets?
It is true, as you said Georg simmel, that a real secret is a secret empty (and a secret vacuum can never be revealed); it is also true that all knowledge about the nature of Berlusconi or Merkel is really a secret vacuum, without secrecy, given that comes from the public sphere; but they uncovered, and WikiLeaks, the secrets of Hillary Clinton was classified, empty means removing any power.
WikiLeaks he has not done any harm to Sarkozy and Merkel, but yes, and far, Clinton and Obama.
What will be the consequences of this wound inflicted to a power so powerful?
It is clear that, in the future, states can no longer put in the network no classified, as it would be as do this in a poster in the street.
But it is also clear that, with current technologies, we cannot expect to keep confidential talks by telephone.
Nothing is easier to find out if and when a Head of State has shifted and it has contacted one of the peers.
How will they keep in the future relationship private and confidential?
I am well aware that, for the moment, my prognosis is about science fiction and, therefore, novelesca, but I imagine to government agents that move inconspicuously in stagecoach with uncontrollable itineraries, carrying messages that have been learned from memory or, as much, hiding some data written on the heels of her shoes.
That information is then, in a single copy, in drawers closed with key: after all, the attempted espionage Watergate had less success that WikiLeaks.
In the past, I have written that technology is now running as a crab, that is to say, backwards.
A century after the wireless telegraph has revolutionized communications, the Internet has become to create a Telegraph with cables (phone).
The video tapes (analogue) had allowed researchers to study film a movie step by step, advancing and receding, discovering all the secrets of the editing, whereas now CDS (digital) just any headway or backtrack from chapter to chapter, i.e. to massive proportions.
With high-speed trains, we can go from Rome to Milan in three hours, while in plane, with movements that entails, we need three and a half hours.
Therefore, there is nothing outside of normal politics and communications they take us back to the cars of horses.
One last comment.
In the past, the press was trying to understand what is secretly plotting in embassies.
Today, there are embassies which call for confidential information to the press.
Climate: the messes of France in their promises of funding
A year after the Copenhagen agreement, it is time to examine whether promises of funding quickly unlocked (so-called fast start or available) made by the developed countries.
And they have revealed the French messes.
In the Copenhagen agreement, the developed countries undertook to provide $30 billion between 2010 and 2012.
The European Union committed itself to provide 7.2 million euros in three years and France earmarked million euros (420 million per year).
During the opening of the COP16, the EU has put on the table its best to convince its partners that its commitment to financing fast start is real: a report detailing the measures its Member States, a press conference, a major event, the distribution of leaflets...
The operation transparency worthwhile result and was appreciated for what it is really: developing countries and civil society would all developed countries do the same and with the same degree of accuracy.
The EU advertises 2010 has released EUR 2.2 billion, which puts it in the right direction towards the fulfilment of its commitment to 7.2 billion in 2012.
But, if we look at the situation closely, things are more complicated.
According to the Copenhagen agreement, the money must be "new and additional" to ensure that we make an additional effort, without harming the official development assistance.
Unfortunately, it has not come to an agreement on which means "new and additional."
When the European Commission proposed harmonization, some Member States, including France, have blocked the procedure.
Today, each person chooses the reference.
For example, the European Commission has taken into account the year 2009: the international funding and add 150 million in three years in terms of funding fast start.
Other countries have adopted similar references in the year or at the level of official development aid.
On the contrary, France believes that the funding of "all new projects" in the year 2010 are "new and additional."
In other words, there is a reference to the cost of previous years and the overall level of official development aid.
In particular, the total amount of aid France to developing countries can remain stable (or even decrease), while intends to respect their commitment in terms of funds' new and additional ..."
Another crucial element, the distribution of grants and loans.
Once again, there is no standard and each person chooses the method of calculation.
Some, such as France, consider that every euro borrowing amounts to a euro donated.
Obviously, this is hard to justify: the effort is not comparable.
Although the use of loans can be justified for certain investments that are profitable (often, projects related to the reduction of emissions which are based on more effective technologies), it is untrue, presenting a euro that will recover as equivalent to a euro dona... as much, just to be paid for their commitments to the cost of the loan to the country that gives the loan (that is, the equivalent to an interest rate).
But France is useful such reasoning: "respect" their commitment of 420 million euros doing a 91.5% of loans (389,8 million euros) and a 8.5% of donations (36.1 billion euros); consult the document from the EU to see it with their own eyes.
It is the only EU country that is so often the loan.
Germany used in a 46%, while Denmark, the Netherlands or Slovakia, among others, respect their commitments with a 100% of donations.
In other words, when the majority of the European Union provides a euro to fulfill their commitment, France only contributes 10 cents and believes that the effort is comparable.
A neat trick!
In short, in its financing fast start, France made a double abuse: on the one hand, in relation to actions at the time and, on the other, in relation to the real financial effort.
Spending only 36.1 million euros, manages to give the impression that spends 420 million "new and additional," as it had promised.
The handling of the Ministry of Finance (which is bercy who has occupied the arbitration) could have a negative impact, both within the EU (why would the other Member States to continue donating when they can simply pay?) and in the negotiations, since developing countries are not fools...
The chapter on the early financing is peanuts, relatively short term, in relation to the whole of the negotiations on the climate.
But it could be a bit more in the vast machine that is the UNFCCC.
Hopefully it otherwise.
Whatever it is, it is vital to learn of this first year of available financing.
Firstly, France could announce a change in the method of calculation for the years 2011 and 2012, with the intention of respecting its commitments and in the same way that other countries of the European Union.
But, especially, France could make moving debates on gambling at stake in relation to the funding in the long term (another crucial area that is currently under discussion): not inevitable for the issue of "additional" or the method for measuring lending.
France could change its stance to become as progressive in relation to this issue as it is with others.
Therefore, we hope the new environment minister, Mrs Kosciusko-Morizet, who will arrive in Cancun next week.
A surprise announcement on the fast start of France and about his view of the "additional" and the use of the loans would help to improve the level of international confidence needed to make progress in the negotiations.
Warning of the pesticides ingested by children
A child of 10 years ingested in a day 81 different chemicals, suggests a study published on Wednesday by the Association générations futures (the former movement for rights and respect for future generations).
The association, who warns that their results "did not have a significant statistical value given the limited number of samples analyzed, but are illustrative of the problems raised," bought in supermarkets in oise and Paris between July and September, which tends to have a child of about ten years in four meals and a snack each day.
These meals taken as a model, who observed the official recommendations (five parts of fruits and vegetables, three of dairy products and 1.5 litres of water a day), as well as sweets, were examined in laboratories in search of chemicals, pesticides, heavy metals and other pollutants.
The balance of plate is overwhelming: 81 chemicals, of which 42 classified as carcinogenic possible or probable and five substances classified as carcinogenic insurance, as well as 37 to act as endocrine disruptors (EP), according to studies of various institutions like the International Agency for Research on Cancer.
"although, in almost all cases, not exceeded the legal limits for each of the chemicals individually, our study clearly shows that the exposure of consumers to pollutants possibly carcinogenic and / or EP is worrying," says the association.
For breakfast, butter and tea with milk contain alone more than a dozen possible carcinogenic waste and three classified as carcinogenic insurance, as well as nearly a score of waste that can only hurt the hormone system.
The apple, imported from Brazil, planned as a snack for the College, contains trace amounts of six chemicals, including a fungicide banned in France.
The same applies to beans from Kenya, including in the food, in which the study has detected traces of a powerful insecticide banned in the EU.
In addition, the Russian steak, the canned tuna and even the loaf of bread or the gum were aderezados with pesticides and other chemicals.
In tap water, the analysis found the presence of nitrates and cloroformo.
At dinner, the slice of salmon was the most "nutritional" with 34 chemical waste identified and even the analysis of the plate of plastic used for heating food in the microwave was not entirely clean.
The final risk that create these "cocktails of pollutants" to the consumer "is probably underestimates," says the study.
The Alliance ecología-les Europe Verts (ee-lv), for its part, has proposed "compared to the seriousness of the situation" a moratorium on the use of pesticides to curb "the increasing diseases of civilisation."
In July, a study by the Food Safety Agency (EASA) indicated the presence of residues of pesticides 365 different identified in the fruit and vegetables consumed in Europe, of which 76 in cereals.
